headline: The 5 Most Interesting Analyst Questions From PulteGroup’s Q4 Earnings Call
summary: PulteGroup’s fourth quarter saw a positive market reaction as the company delivered revenue above Wall Street’s expectations, despite notable declines in both sales and profit margins. Management attributed the quarter’s performance to continued strength in its geographically diverse operations—especially in the Midwest, Northeast, and Florida—where demand has held up better than in Texas and Western markets. headline: Del Webb Announces First Active Adult Community in Bridgeland®
summary: HOUSTON, February 05, 2026--Del Webb, America’s leading builder of active adult communities for those 55+, today announced Del Webb Bridgeland, a new 190-acre community planned for Bridgeland, the 11,500-acre master planned community in northwest Houston developed by Howard Hughes Communities™.
